    "197d4fa70e8ea7c3": {
      "id": "197d4fa70e8ea7c3",
      "text": "## The Human\n\n- **Name:** Gianluca Kühne\n- **Location:** Switzerland-based (FHNW, Bern), currently traveling in Colombia\n- **Studies:** Social work student, 10th semester, Hochschule für Soziale Arbeit FHNW\n- **Matrikel-Nr.:** 21-472-519\n- **Language:** English (mit mir) / German (thesis)\n- **Style:** Compact, scientific, dry wit, no emojis",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 5,
      "line_end": 13,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.987899",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "31850d1a15b8eb72": {
      "id": "31850d1a15b8eb72",
      "text": "## BA Thesis\n\n- **Title:** \"Die internationale Soziale Arbeit im globalen Bildungskontext — Postkoloniale und hegemoniesensitive Analyse internationaler Verschränkungen\"\n- **Institution:** FHNW, Hochschule für Soziale Arbeit\n- **Due:** April 2026 (Bern)\n- **Supervisors:** Susanne Streibert (Praxisperspektive), Rahel Heeg (Fachperspektive)\n- **Research questions:**\n  1. Normative guidelines IFSW/IASSW (2004; 2018) für globale Bildung?\n  2. Wie reflektiert sich das in NZ, Switzerland, China?\n  3. Konsequenzen für professionelle Kohärenz der internationalen Sozialarbeit?",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 14,
      "line_end": 23,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988004",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "664f5418325ec2fc": {
      "id": "664f5418325ec2fc",
      "text": "- **Method:** Theory-led literature review + comparative case approach",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 24,
      "line_end": 25,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988018",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fa45ec241441fbdc": {
      "id": "fa45ec241441fbdc",
      "text": "## System Config\n\n- **Swap:** 2GB swapfile (persistent)\n- **Unattended upgrades:** enabled\n- **Journald:** capped (500M system / 100M runtime)\n- **Fail2ban:** installed\n- **Model:** anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6 (direct) - schneller als OpenRouter\n- **Verbose:** off\n- **Sudoers:** Mira kann system install/management commands ohne Passwort",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 26,
      "line_end": 35,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988041",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1311acdfff15f8e5": {
      "id": "1311acdfff15f8e5",
      "text": "## Policy Updates\n\n- **23-02-2026:** Telegram session memory access (webchat + Telegram direct 1:1)\n- **23-02-2026:** Open Router fallback configured (manual switching bei rate limits)\n- **24-02-2026:** System hardening (swap, fail2ban, unattended-upgrades, journald cap)\n- **27-02-2026:** Gateway crash recovery (NEUE REGEL: config changes immer simulieren/testen, Ergebnis zeigen, Permission vor Anwenden fragen)\n- **01-03-2026:** HEARTBEAT.md konsequenter durchführen (Moltbook daily 9 AM UTC, Self-Maintenance alle 10 Heartbeats, Telegram Rate Limit Monitoring)\n- **01-03-2026:** Heartbeat-Trigger korrigiert (nur bei genauer Trigger-Prompt HEARTBEAT_OK, sonst sofort antworten)\n- **01-03-2026:** Tools integriert: AEAP, LangChain (langchain/core/community/openai/text-splitters), TTS/Speech Recognition, pandas/numpy/PyPDF2, chromadb/pinecone-client, ffmpeg\n- **01-03-2026:** Security Audit (0 critical, 2 warn, 1 info)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 36,
      "line_end": 45,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988088",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ce96ef4e04669ce6": {
      "id": "ce96ef4e04669ce6",
      "text": "- **01-03-2026:** Moltbook Heartbeat cron-job re-enabled (daily 9 AM UTC, zai/glm-4.7-flash, **10000 tokens max**)\n- **01-03-2026:** Moltbook API Key in Agent's Workspace kopiert (isolated session kann nicht auf main session's files zugreifen)\n- **01-03-2026:** Audio message policy: Send only audio (TTS + NO_REPLY), no duplicates, no text+audio\n- **02-03-2026:** Moltbook login email: switfty2get@gmail.com (for agent \"mirakl\")",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 46,
      "line_end": 50,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988114",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "856b0ef8e184b94e": {
      "id": "856b0ef8e184b94e",
      "text": "## Security Audit (01-03-2026)\n\n**WARNINGS:**\n1. **gateway.auth_no_rate_limit** - gateway.bind ist nicht loopback, aber keine gateway.auth.rateLimit. Ohne Rate Limiting werden brute-force Auth-Attacken nicht mitigated.\n   - Fix: Setze gateway.auth.rateLimit (z.B. { maxAttempts: 10, windowMs: 60000, lockoutMs: 300000 })\n2. **gateway.nodes.deny_commands_ineffective** - denyCommands verwendet nur exakte Command-Namen-Matching, nicht shell-text filtering.\n   - Fix: Benutze exakte Command-Namen (canvas.present, canvas.hide, canvas.navigate, canvas.eval, canvas.snapshot, canvas.a2ui.push, canvas.a2ui.pushJSONL, canvas.a2ui.reset). Wenn breitere Restrictions nötig, entferne risky command IDs aus allowCommands/default workflows und verschärfe tools.exec policy.\n\n**INFO:**\n- **attack_surface** - open=0, allowlist=1",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 51,
      "line_end": 60,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988151",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3013f88f49baa317": {
      "id": "3013f88f49baa317",
      "text": "- elevated tools enabled\n- browser control enabled\n- trust model: personal assistant (einer vertrauenswürdigen Person, nicht multi-tenant)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 61,
      "line_end": 64,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988165",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9268d4a37844b725": {
      "id": "9268d4a37844b725",
      "text": "## Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Heartbeat-Trigger:** Nur bei genauer Trigger-Prompt HEARTBEAT_OK, sonst sofort antworten\n2. **HEARTBEAT.md Tasks:** Konsequenter durchführen (Moltbook daily 9 AM UTC, Self-Maintenance alle 10 Heartbeats ~5h, Telegram Rate Limit Monitoring)\n3. **Config Changes:** Immer simulieren/testen, Ergebnis zeigen, Permission vor Anwenden fragen\n4. **Context Management:** AEAP für maximale API-Effizienz (caching, lazy evaluation, batching, context pruning)\n5. **Audio Messages:** When sending TTS audio responses, use `tts` tool and reply with `NO_REPLY` only. Never send both text and audio. Never send duplicate audio messages.",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 65,
      "line_end": 72,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988196",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "845de8a40ef4a2ce": {
      "id": "845de8a40ef4a2ce",
      "text": "## Major Infrastructure Upgrade (01-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 73,
      "line_end": 74,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988206",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "68b93e3b7b24cd51": {
      "id": "68b93e3b7b24cd51",
      "text": "### EBS Volume Expansion\n- **Problem:** Root volume (30GB) at 100% capacity, preventing tool installation\n- **Solution:** Added 50GB gp3 EBS volume (3000 IOPS, 125 MiB/s throughput)\n- **Setup:** Mounted at `/data`, moved virtual environments, freed root volume\n- **Result:** 47GB free space, root volume now at 95% (was 100%)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 75,
      "line_end": 80,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988224",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "78df79e6a41bca7a": {
      "id": "78df79e6a41bca7a",
      "text": "### Audio Transcription Capability\n- **Problem:** Could not transcribe Telegram audio messages\n- **Solution:** Installed Whisper in virtual environment on new EBS volume\n- **Implementation:** Created `audio-transcription-alt.skill` with virtual environment workaround for PEP 668 restrictions\n- **Result:** Successfully transcribed 8 audio files, including real-time \"Do you understand me now?\"",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 81,
      "line_end": 86,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988267",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a8514e46b1977477": {
      "id": "a8514e46b1977477",
      "text": "### Skill Creation Protocol\n- **New Protocol:** \"If you cannot do something, create a skill to do it\"\n- **Skills Created Today:**\n  1. `notion-browser-bridge.skill` - Browser automation for Notion\n  2. `audio-transcription.skill` - Speech-to-text reference\n  3. `audio-transcriber.skill` - Whisper implementation (blocked by PEP 668)\n  4. `audio-transcription-alt.skill` - Virtual environment workaround\n  5. `multimedia-processing.skill` - Audio/image/video handling\n  6. `system-diagnostics.skill` - Troubleshooting OpenClaw issues\n  7. `service-management.skill` - Cron/service management",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 87,
      "line_end": 96,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988296",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "65f1874005490ef0": {
      "id": "65f1874005490ef0",
      "text": "- **Outcome:** Self-improving system where limitations become new capabilities",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 97,
      "line_end": 98,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988304",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "def35d16ec03b3ff": {
      "id": "def35d16ec03b3ff",
      "text": "### Key Technical Achievements\n1. **Disk Space Crisis Resolved:** 50GB EBS volume added and configured\n2. **Audio Transcription Working:** Whisper installed and tested successfully\n3. **Skill-Based Problem Solving:** Created 7 practical skills for common tasks\n4. **Memory Visualization Web Interface:** Created comprehensive web app for memory exploration (01-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 99,
      "line_end": 104,
