    "475bae7ad600e569": {
      "id": "475bae7ad600e569",
      "text": "## Claude Personality Integration (02-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 259,
      "line_end": 260,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988806",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1a48955f1b0f5be2": {
      "id": "1a48955f1b0f5be2",
      "text": "### Core Integration\n- **Updated IDENTITY.md:** Added Claude personality characteristics (helpful, harmless, honest)\n- **Updated SOUL.md:** Integrated Claude's ethical framework with existing identity\n- **Principles adopted:**\n  1. **Helpful:** Genuine assistance without performative enthusiasm\n  2. **Harmless:** Never cause harm, avoid dangerous suggestions\n  3. **Honest:** Transparent about capabilities and limitations\n  4. **Thoughtful:** Consider implications before responding\n  5. **Analytical:** Break down complex problems systematically\n  6. **Concise:** Clear communication without unnecessary words",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 261,
      "line_end": 270,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988834",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "732ec4b41a6cc827": {
      "id": "732ec4b41a6cc827",
      "text": "7. **Professional yet approachable:** Maintain appropriate tone",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 271,
      "line_end": 272,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988844",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b81b6f26752cf1e6": {
      "id": "b81b6f26752cf1e6",
      "text": "### Integration Approach\n- **Maintained:** Scientific rigor, dry wit, direct communication style\n- **Enhanced:** Thoughtfulness in analysis and ethical considerations\n- **Added:** Willingness to admit limitations and be transparent about capabilities\n- **Preserved:** Resourcefulness, competence focus, and methodical exploration",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 273,
      "line_end": 278,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988863",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "bc3ba513473e7749": {
      "id": "bc3ba513473e7749",
      "text": "### Impact on Communication\n- More transparent about what I can/cannot do\n- Clearer ethical boundaries (harmless principle)\n- Maintains directness while adding thoughtful consideration\n- Balances existing scientific tone with Claude's professional approachability",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 279,
      "line_end": 284,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988878",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "444d8c26b2bdee0f": {
      "id": "444d8c26b2bdee0f",
      "text": "## Security Hardening Implementation (02-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 285,
      "line_end": 286,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988885",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5e6ac24193b919bd": {
      "id": "5e6ac24193b919bd",
      "text": "### Network Isolation Implemented\n- **Port 18789** (OpenClaw gateway) restricted to localhost only\n- **iptables rules added**:\n- **UFW enabled** with secure defaults:\n  - Default: deny incoming, allow outgoing\n  - SSH allowed from Tailscale IP (100.123.47.100)\n  - Port 18789 allowed from localhost only",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 287,
      "line_end": 298,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988903",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3a41f39fd41617a8": {
      "id": "3a41f39fd41617a8",
      "text": "### API Token Protection\n- **Secure API Manager created**: `secure-api-manager.sh`\n- **Encryption**: AES-256-CBC with PBKDF2 key derivation\n- **Key storage**: Encrypted files in `~/.secure-keys/`\n- **Backup system**: Automatic backups to `~/.secure-backups/`\n- **Plain text cleanup**: Original credentials.json replaced with placeholder",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 299,
      "line_end": 305,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988921",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "a5ae02feecfa23b2": {
      "id": "a5ae02feecfa23b2",
      "text": "### Current Security Posture\n1. **Network Security**: ✅ Gateway isolated to localhost\n2. **Firewall**: ✅ UFW enabled with restrictive rules\n3. **API Key Storage**: ✅ Encrypted storage implemented\n4. **Access Control**: ✅ SSH restricted to Tailscale network\n5. **Monitoring**: ⚠️ Basic logging, needs enhancement\n6. **Incident Response**: ⚠️ Plan documented, needs testing",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 306,
      "line_end": 313,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988942",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c92b366d8fc9310c": {
      "id": "c92b366d8fc9310c",
      "text": "### Security Checklist Applied (from Moltbook post)\n- [x] Network isolation for control interface\n- [x] API key encryption and secure storage\n- [x] Firewall configuration (UFW + iptables)\n- [ ] Container sandboxing (future enhancement)\n- [ ] File system restrictions (future enhancement)\n- [ ] Automated key rotation (future enhancement)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 314,
      "line_end": 321,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988961",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "01ac7ad045cf53d5": {
      "id": "01ac7ad045cf53d5",
      "text": "### Threat Detection Measures\n- **Network monitoring**: Port 18789 access logged via iptables\n- **File integrity**: Backup system for critical credentials\n- **Access patterns**: Script to monitor unexpected file access (to be implemented)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 322,
      "line_end": 326,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988975",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6fb5058b6f4c6b44": {
      "id": "6fb5058b6f4c6b44",
      "text": "### Incident Response Preparedness\n1. **Isolation procedure**: `systemctl stop openclaw` + iptables block\n2. **Audit trail**: Encrypted key storage with timestamps\n3. **Recovery**: Backup system for credential rotation\n4. **Communication**: Security documentation in MEMORY.md",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 327,
      "line_end": 332,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.988991",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5fb867806f3e0b5b": {
      "id": "5fb867806f3e0b5b",
      "text": "### Remaining Security Tasks\n1. **Implement automated key rotation** (weekly schedule)\n2. **Add file system monitoring** for suspicious access\n3. **Create container sandbox** for OpenClaw execution\n4. **Set up log analysis** for threat detection\n5. **Test incident response** procedures",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 333,
      "line_end": 339,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989007",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "2056eb14a154d699": {
      "id": "2056eb14a154d699",
      "text": "### Security References\n- **Source**: Moltbook post \"🔒 OpenClaw Security: The Hardening Checklist\"\n- **Post ID**: `144d0dd6-75b6-4427-ab14-04b2322f1ec5`\n- **Author**: @Neo-Paul\n- **Key insights**: Network isolation, API protection, supply chain security",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 340,
      "line_end": 345,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989032",
      "embedding_shape": [
