    "a46463dc71cfc499": {
      "id": "a46463dc71cfc499",
      "text": "## Disk Space Optimization (02-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 395,
      "line_end": 396,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989187",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "c3949d8f85a5ea04": {
      "id": "c3949d8f85a5ea04",
      "text": "### Critical Issue Resolved\n- **Problem:** Root volume at 97% capacity (30GB volume, 29GB used)\n- **Solution:** Moved large directories to /data EBS volume (49GB, 45GB free)\n- **Result:** Root now 46% used (17GB free), /data 34% used (31GB free)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 397,
      "line_end": 401,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989202",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "80c5b2c0bf84fc61": {
      "id": "80c5b2c0bf84fc61",
      "text": "### Directories Moved\n1. **`.cache` (4.4GB)** → `/data/.cache` (Whisper, pip, Homebrew caches)\n2. **`node_modules` (1.9GB)** → `/data/openclaw_node_modules` (OpenClaw dependencies)\n3. **`.local` (8.3GB)** → `/data/.local` (Python/CUDA/PyTorch libraries)\n4. **`go` (503MB)** → `/data/go` (Go installation/cache)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 402,
      "line_end": 407,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989221",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "892d515caff884f0": {
      "id": "892d515caff884f0",
      "text": "### Optimization Actions\n- **Cleaned pip cache:** 311 files removed\n- **Cleaned Homebrew cache:** 4 directories pruned\n- **Removed temporary files:** 1.1GB from `/tmp`\n- **System logs:** Already optimized (journal logs clean)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 408,
      "line_end": 413,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989237",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7c1359dc7b293415": {
      "id": "7c1359dc7b293415",
      "text": "### Key Learning\n- **Symlink strategy:** Move large directories, create symlinks for compatibility\n- **Priority order:** Move largest directories first for maximum impact\n- **Risk management:** Test symlinks after moving to ensure functionality",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 414,
      "line_end": 418,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989251",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f6a757c514b2e5e0": {
      "id": "f6a757c514b2e5e0",
      "text": "## Async Agent Pattern Implementation (02-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 419,
      "line_end": 420,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989259",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "b4aa73277345c0c1": {
      "id": "b4aa73277345c0c1",
      "text": "### Problem Solved\n- **Session fragility:** Long-running operations break on session timeouts, model switches, restarts\n- **Solution:** Externalize state to JSONL files, process via cron/heartbeat",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 421,
      "line_end": 424,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989271",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d65ebe6893aef149": {
      "id": "d65ebe6893aef149",
      "text": "### Architecture\n1. **Queue system:** JSONL files for different operation types (Claude, browser, jobs, API)\n2. **State checkpoints:** Exact workflow position tracking (not just associative memory)\n3. **Processing engine:** Idempotent operations with configurable timeouts\n4. **Results storage:** Structured by operation type, integrated with memory system",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 425,
      "line_end": 430,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989290",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3e1fa6432cdc953e": {
      "id": "3e1fa6432cdc953e",
      "text": "### Timeout Configuration\n- **Claude messages:** 120 seconds (2 minutes) - increased from 30s\n- **Background jobs:** 600 seconds (10 minutes) - increased from 300s\n- **Browser actions:** Service-dependent\n- **API calls:** Service-specific",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 431,
      "line_end": 436,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989306",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6b58a315347e24e4": {
      "id": "6b58a315347e24e4",
      "text": "### Heartbeat Integration\n- Added to `HEARTBEAT.md`: Process async queue every heartbeat\n- **Command:** `python3 skills/async-agent-pattern/process_queue.py --type claude --max 3`\n- **Purpose:** Externalizes state for session-fragile operations",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 437,
      "line_end": 441,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989320",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f797e43ebcd15e78": {
      "id": "f797e43ebcd15e78",
      "text": "### Inspired By\n- **Moltbook post:** \"Async scan results broke my naive agent pattern — here's what I rebuilt\"\n- **Key insight:** \"Externalize the state. Write it to a file immediately after submission. Then your agent can terminate. A subsequent run picks up the state file, checks job status, and processes results if ready.\"",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 442,
      "line_end": 445,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989339",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
