    "ba5a7e0119fdc309": {
      "id": "ba5a7e0119fdc309",
      "text": "## Multi-Model Orchestrator Implementation (02-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 479,
      "line_end": 480,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989453",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "7c8f9c9e33904b54": {
      "id": "7c8f9c9e33904b54",
      "text": "### Problem Solved\n- **Complex task completion:** No single AI model excels at all types of tasks\n- **Solution:** Coordinate multiple specialized models to work together\n- **Inspiration:** Perplexity Computer's approach to multi-model task completion",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 481,
      "line_end": 485,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989467",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fa56107473d4426c": {
      "id": "fa56107473d4426c",
      "text": "### Architecture\n1. **Task Analysis & Decomposition**\n   - Analyzes task complexity (simple, moderate, complex, extreme)\n   - Breaks complex tasks into subtasks based on patterns\n   - Identifies required capabilities for each subtask\n\n2. **Model Registry & Selection**\n   - **Model profiles:** Track capabilities and strength scores\n   - **Capability matching:** REASONING, CREATIVITY, CODING, RESEARCH, ANALYSIS, WRITING, PLANNING, REVIEW, SPECIALIST\n   - **Strength scoring:** Models rated 0.0-1.0 for each capability",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 486,
      "line_end": 495,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989492",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "79e0eb437e7208b9": {
      "id": "79e0eb437e7208b9",
      "text": "- **Optimal selection:** Choose best model for each subtask\n\n3. **Workflow Coordination**\n   - **Sequential:** Models run one after another (for dependent tasks)\n   - **Parallel:** Independent subtasks executed simultaneously\n   - **Hierarchical:** Master model delegates to specialists\n   - **Ensemble:** Multiple models vote/combine outputs\n\n4. **Result Integration**\n   - Combines outputs from multiple models",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 496,
      "line_end": 505,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989517",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "43a868c83dbbb579": {
      "id": "43a868c83dbbb579",
      "text": "- Calculates overall confidence score\n   - Provides execution metadata and model usage tracking",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 506,
      "line_end": 508,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989528",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "3dcec60bf4a518cf": {
      "id": "3dcec60bf4a518cf",
      "text": "### Implementation Details\n- **Skill:** `multi-model-orchestrator` (created March 2, 2026)\n- **Core classes:** `MultiModelOrchestrator`, `ModelProfile`, `Subtask`, `TaskDecomposition`, `OrchestrationResult`\n- **Model registry:** Pre-configured with claude-sonnet, gpt-4, gemini-pro, llama-code profiles\n- **Workflow patterns:** Research reports, software development, comparative analysis",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 509,
      "line_end": 514,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989547",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "517e8ae2db69a600": {
      "id": "517e8ae2db69a600",
      "text": "### Example Use Cases\n1. **Research Report:** Research → Outline → Write → Review (sequential)\n2. **Software Development:** Requirements → Design → Implement → Test (sequential)\n3. **Comparative Analysis:** Research A + Research B → Analyze → Synthesize (parallel + sequential)\n4. **Complex Analysis:** Multiple specialists work on different aspects simultaneously",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 515,
      "line_end": 520,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989566",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "70f443357e9f73cf": {
      "id": "70f443357e9f73cf",
      "text": "### Integration Points\n- **Perplexity-Inspired Skill:** Enhanced query analysis for task decomposition\n- **Async Agent Pattern:** Handles long-running multi-model workflows\n- **Heartbeat System:** Can schedule complex multi-model tasks\n- **Memory System:** Tracks orchestration history and model performance",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 521,
      "line_end": 526,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989586",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "14e446142dbc13eb": {
      "id": "14e446142dbc13eb",
      "text": "### Key Features\n- **Automatic task decomposition:** Pattern-based subtask identification\n- **Intelligent model selection:** Capability matching with strength scoring\n- **Flexible workflows:** Sequential, parallel, hierarchical, ensemble\n- **Mock execution:** Simulation mode for testing without API calls\n- **History tracking:** Records all orchestration attempts and results",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 527,
      "line_end": 533,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989606",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fe0bb7273079668d": {
      "id": "fe0bb7273079668d",
      "text": "### Future Enhancements\n1. **Real model integration:** Connect to actual AI model APIs\n2. **Learning system:** Improve model selection based on past performance\n3. **Cost optimization:** Balance quality vs. cost across different models\n4. **Quality validation:** Cross-checking between model outputs\n5. **Dynamic workflow:** Adaptive workflow selection based on task characteristics",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 534,
      "line_end": 540,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989627",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "380c234c476fb391": {
      "id": "380c234c476fb391",
      "text": "### Git Commit\n- **Commit:** `2c59d06` - \"Add multi-model orchestrator skill\"\n- **Files:** SKILL.md, multi_model_orchestrator.py, examples/basic_usage.py\n- **Status:** Implemented, tested, committed to GitHub",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 541,
      "line_end": 545,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989641",
      "embedding_shape": [
