    "7e1c43cb1d176f2e": {
      "id": "7e1c43cb1d176f2e",
      "text": "## Entrosana.com Dashboard Connection Setup (02-03-2026)",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 546,
      "line_end": 547,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989649",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "18ecb35600bffffa": {
      "id": "18ecb35600bffffa",
      "text": "### **Architecture:**\n1. **OpenClaw Gateway**: Port 18789 (local)\n2. **NGINX Reverse Proxy**: Port 443 (HTTPS) → Port 18789\n3. **DNS**: entrosana.com → 18.225.98.79 (EC2 public IP)\n4. **SSL**: Let's Encrypt certificate via Certbot",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 548,
      "line_end": 553,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989665",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "fe769d002691e32d": {
      "id": "fe769d002691e32d",
      "text": "### **Firewall Layers (All Must Allow):**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 554,
      "line_end": 555,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989673",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ea0e4be1176ab9f8": {
      "id": "ea0e4be1176ab9f8",
      "text": "#### **1. AWS Security Group (EC2 Level)**\n- **Port 443**: Allow 0.0.0.0/0 (HTTPS)\n- **Port 18789**: Allow specific IPs or 0.0.0.0/0\n- **Check**: EC2 → Security Groups → Inbound Rules",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 556,
      "line_end": 560,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989702",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "d4e4aad66a08c703": {
      "id": "d4e4aad66a08c703",
      "text": "#### **2. AWS Network ACL (Subnet Level - STATEFUL)**\n- **INBOUND**: Must allow port 443 AND destination port (18789 after proxy)\n- **OUTBOUND**: Must allow ephemeral ports (1024-65535) for responses\n- **Common Issue**: Rule 101 too restrictive (only port 443, blocks 18789)\n- **Fix**: Change to \"All Traffic\" or add rule for port 18789\n- **Check**: VPC → Network ACLs → Associated with subnet",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 561,
      "line_end": 567,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989729",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "765c9fc0b59b85f9": {
      "id": "765c9fc0b59b85f9",
      "text": "#### **3. Instance Firewall (UFW)**\n- **Port 443**: `sudo ufw allow 443/tcp`\n- **Port 18789**: `sudo ufw allow 18789/tcp`\n- **Check**: `sudo ufw status verbose`\n- **Default**: deny (incoming) - must explicitly allow ports",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 568,
      "line_end": 573,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989745",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "46ba8fd023193c01": {
      "id": "46ba8fd023193c01",
      "text": "### **NGINX Configuration:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 574,
      "line_end": 599,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989757",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "6ed4cedd56a63617": {
      "id": "6ed4cedd56a63617",
      "text": "### **Diagnostic Commands:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 600,
      "line_end": 601,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989763",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9a8e2ed34b0c9a31": {
      "id": "9a8e2ed34b0c9a31",
      "text": "#### **Check Connectivity:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 602,
      "line_end": 619,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989771",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "70dc473ad01ebc57": {
      "id": "70dc473ad01ebc57",
      "text": "#### **Check AWS Configuration:**\n- **Security Group**: Port 443 allows 0.0.0.0/0\n- **NACL**: Both inbound AND outbound allow traffic\n- **Route Table**: 0.0.0.0/0 → Internet Gateway",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 620,
      "line_end": 624,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989783",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "1e0f23162864baa9": {
      "id": "1e0f23162864baa9",
      "text": "### **Common Error Patterns:**",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 625,
      "line_end": 626,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989791",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "462565976f9678d6": {
      "id": "462565976f9678d6",
      "text": "#### **\"disconnected (1006): no reason\"**\n- WebSocket connection failing\n- Check NGINX WebSocket headers (`Upgrade`, `Connection`)\n- Check gateway WebSocket support",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 627,
      "line_end": 631,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989803",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "dd94588c6a9de477": {
      "id": "dd94588c6a9de477",
      "text": "#### **\"net::ERR_CONNECTION_TIMED_OUT\"**\n- Firewall blocking at some layer\n- Check all 3 firewalls: Security Group, NACL, UFW\n- NACL outbound ephemeral ports often missed",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 632,
      "line_end": 636,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989815",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f0864bb9e79824da": {
      "id": "f0864bb9e79824da",
      "text": "#### **No errors but no connection**\n- NACL inbound too restrictive (only port 443, blocks proxied port 18789)\n- UFW missing port 443 rule",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 637,
      "line_end": 640,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989826",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "877caa6a2dc6130c": {
      "id": "877caa6a2dc6130c",
      "text": "### **Quick Fix Checklist:**\n1. ✅ **Security Group**: Port 443 allows 0.0.0.0/0\n2. ✅ **NACL Inbound**: Allows destination port (18789 after proxy)\n3. ✅ **NACL Outbound**: Allows ephemeral ports (1024-65535)\n4. ✅ **UFW**: `sudo ufw allow 443/tcp`\n5. ✅ **NGINX**: Running and configured\n6. ✅ **Gateway**: Running on port 18789",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 641,
      "line_end": 648,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989845",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "94aea98ea2dbfede": {
      "id": "94aea98ea2dbfede",
      "text": "### **Self-Repair Protocol:**\nIf dashboard goes down:\n1. Run diagnostic commands above\n2. Check each firewall layer\n3. Most likely: NACL outbound or UFW port 443\n4. Apply fixes from this memory entry",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 649,
      "line_end": 655,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.989859",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
