    "474c9d660b0ae02f": {
      "id": "474c9d660b0ae02f",
      "text": "### Tagging System Nuances & Error Analysis (03-03-2026)\n- **Discovery**: Keyword-based tagging labels library files as `[ERROR]` (935 files tagged)\n- **Analysis**: Most are pip cache modules with standard error handling code, not actual error logs\n- **Safety assessment**: 0 files safely deletable, 933 unsafe (libraries), 2 need review\n- **Key insight**: Tagging systems need content-aware classification, not just keyword matching\n- **Action**: Keep libraries intact, system already clean via 5/20 retention policy\n- **Lesson**: When analyzing \"error\" files, distinguish between error documentation and actual error logs",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 694,
      "line_end": 701,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.990006",
      "embedding_shape": [
