    "50bf8784931a3b7d": {
      "id": "50bf8784931a3b7d",
      "text": "#### System Service Cleanup\n- **Issue**: `mirakl.service` failing repeatedly with \"Changing to the requested working directory failed: No such file or directory\"\n- **Root cause**: Leftover systemd service from previous Telegram userbot setup (`/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/telethon` directory no longer exists)\n- **Resolution**:\n  1. Stopped service: `sudo systemctl stop mirakl.service`\n  2. Disabled service: `sudo systemctl disable mirakl.service`\n  3. Reset failure counter: `sudo systemctl reset-failed mirakl.service`\n- **Status**: Service now inactive (dead), disabled, will not restart automatically\n- **Rationale**: Moltbook functionality now handled by cron job (`0 9 * * *`), Telegram automation via OpenClaw gateway\n- **Optional cleanup**: Service file (`/etc/systemd/system/mirakl.service`) and virtual environment (`/home/ubuntu/.venv/telethon`) can be removed",
      "source": "MEMORY.md",
      "line_start": 854,
      "line_end": 863,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.990511",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "9ceea60a91c37cfd": {
      "id": "9ceea60a91c37cfd",
