    },
    "561293f24baf6671": {
      "id": "561293f24baf6671",
      "text": "### **Problem Resolution:**\n- **Before fix**: 935 files tagged `[ERROR]` (51% of workspace) - excessive false positives\n- **After fix**: **14 files tagged `[ERROR]`** (0.8% of workspace) - accurate error detection\n- **Improvement**: **98.5% reduction** in false positive error tags",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 4,
      "line_end": 8,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993142",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "e2b985286ff0e3c6": {
      "id": "e2b985286ff0e3c6",
      "text": "### **Root Cause Analysis:**\n1. **Simple keyword matching**: Original `TAG_RULES` included `\"error\"`, `\"fail\"`, `\"issue\"` as keywords\n2. **Library code triggering**: Python library files (`site-packages/`, `.venv-*/`) containing error handling functions\n3. **False positives**: Function definitions like `def handle_error()`, `class Error:` were tagged as errors\n4. **Memory files documenting errors**: Actual system errors in memory logs were correctly tagged",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 9,
      "line_end": 14,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993162",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "ec676f2804f8c618": {
