    "f05f57e0ee4886b6": {
      "id": "f05f57e0ee4886b6",
      "text": "#### **1. Three-Layer Error Detection:**\n1. **Path filtering**: Exclude library directories from error tagging\n2. **Pattern matching**: Only match actual error patterns (`ERROR:`, `Traceback`, etc.)\n3. **Context awareness**: Skip error tagging for library function definitions",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 128,
      "line_end": 132,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993319",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "5b71f3b908f8d22d": {
      "id": "5b71f3b908f8d22d",
      "text": "#### **2. Fallback Safety:**\n- Original `tag_everything.py` preserved as backup\n- All modifications are backward compatible\n- Can revert to previous behavior if needed",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 133,
      "line_end": 137,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993330",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f832987967e13596": {
      "id": "f832987967e13596",
      "text": "#### **3. Monitoring Capability:**\n- Created analysis script to track error tag counts\n- Can monitor for new error patterns\n- Generates improvement reports",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 138,
      "line_end": 142,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993340",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "f2688d565e67acac": {
      "id": "f2688d565e67acac",
      "text": "### **Lessons Learned:**",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 143,
      "line_end": 144,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993346",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "98204dac23286724": {
      "id": "98204dac23286724",
      "text": "#### **1. Tagging System Design:**\n- **Keyword lists need curation**: Generic words like \"error\" cause false positives\n- **Context matters**: File path provides valuable context for tagging decisions\n- **Pattern specificity**: `\"error:\"` (at start of line) vs `\"error\"` (anywhere)",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 145,
      "line_end": 149,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993359",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "71df50ecceb8bbd1": {
      "id": "71df50ecceb8bbd1",
      "text": "#### **2. Library Code Handling:**\n- **Standard directories**: `site-packages/`, `.venv-*/` contain library code, not user errors\n- **Function definitions**: `def handle_error()`, `class Error:` are library constructs\n- **Import statements**: `import errors`, `from errors import` are library imports",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 150,
      "line_end": 154,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993373",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
    "073adff69fad9825": {
      "id": "073adff69fad9825",
      "text": "#### **3. User Experience:**\n- **Accuracy over coverage**: Better to miss some errors than tag everything as error\n- **Transparent reporting**: Show what was tagged and why\n- **Incremental improvement**: Start strict, loosen if missing real errors",
      "source": "memory/2026-03-03.md",
      "line_start": 155,
      "line_end": 159,
      "timestamp": "2026-03-05T06:01:50.993387",
      "embedding_shape": [
        384
      ]
    },
